@KMORJ

Virus or no virus...you may wanna look up the term "bricked". Bricking any hardware requires that piece of hardware to have firmware...which your computer does not. And generally hardware that is considered bricked is typically not recoverable especially not as easily as reinstalling software to it....Just a heads up!

Granted, bad choice of words.  It just came down to losing too many vital windows components and having to do a fresh install, which I didnt have a backup disc for.  Your right though, it was a bad choice of words, I appologize

The video quality is great, for a cam at least.
But the sound quality is TERRIBLE. Echoing, high bass, washed-out audio. I got about 15 minutes in before I closed out smplayer because I couldn't hear half of what anyone was saying due to the audio. I tried playing around with some of the audio settings to see if there was someway to improve the audio, but it sill sucked.

As I said, the video quality is great, but unless you have some subtitle track for this... avoid.
